"MEMORIAL DAY ... WHAT IT MEANS TO ME" by Prince Handley

My brother, Eric, died in Italy at Salerno Beach after fighting in North Africa and Sicily. 

At Salerno Beach, Italy, my brother and his men were hemmed in by a sniper. They did not know exactly where the sniper was hidden. My brother willingly - and decisively - advanced to draw the sniper's gunfire so that his men could see from where the sniper was shooting.
